[623.682129, "o", "\u001b[4mPASSWD\u001b[24m(1)                       User Commands                      \u001b[4mPASSWD\u001b[24m(1)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       passwd - change user password\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mpasswd \u001b[22m[\u001b[4moptions\u001b[24m] [\u001b[4mLOGIN\u001b[24m]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       The \u001b[1mpasswd \u001b[22mcommand changes passwords for user accounts. A normal user\u001b[m\r\n       may only change the password for their own account, while the\u001b[m\r\n       superuser may change the password for any account.  \u001b[1mpasswd \u001b[22malso\u001b[m\r\n       changes the account or associated password validity period.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n   \u001b[1mPassword Changes\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       The user is first prompted for their old password, if one is present.\u001b[m\r\n       This password is then encrypted and compared against the stored\u001b[m\r\n       password. The user has only one chance to enter the correct password.\u001b[m\r\n       The superuser is permitted to bypass this step so that forgotten\u001b[m\r\n       passwords may be changed.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       After the password has been entered, password aging information is\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page passwd(1) line 1 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[626.963942, "o", "\r\u001b[K\u001b[?1l\u001b>\u001b[?1049l\u001b[23;0;0t"]
